00:22:22.630 --> 00:22:24.880
on Wake Island.

00:22:24.880 --> 00:22:27.070
And if you've ever heard
of it, you go to Hawaii,

00:22:27.070 --> 00:22:30.239
and then you go that far again,
another 5,000 nautical miles,

00:22:30.239 --> 00:22:31.780
out in the middle
of nowhere, there's

00:22:31.780 --> 00:22:34.540
an atoll that's
tactically important.

00:22:34.540 --> 00:22:36.130
You can refuel a ship there.

00:22:36.130 --> 00:22:38.830
And that's where they used
to refuel the flying boats,

00:22:38.830 --> 00:22:41.800
the Boeing clipper airplane.

00:22:41.800 --> 00:22:46.330
And anyway, they were bombed on
December 8th, 1941, which was

00:22:46.330 --> 00:22:48.040
December 7th in Pearl Harbor.

00:22:48.040 --> 00:22:51.536
It's the same day because of
the International Date Line.

00:22:51.536 --> 00:22:53.410
Wake is beyond on the
International Date Line

00:22:53.410 --> 00:22:54.770
when flying east to west.

00:22:54.770 --> 00:22:58.450
And so he was a prisoner
of war for four years.

00:22:58.450 --> 00:23:02.364
If you get a chance to be
a prisoner of war, don't.

00:23:02.364 --> 00:23:02.864
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:02.864 --> 00:23:05.140
It just sucked.

00:23:05.140 --> 00:23:09.760
But my mom was graduated
in 1942, that spring.

00:23:09.760 --> 00:23:13.360
Her boyfriend had disappeared.

00:23:13.360 --> 00:23:14.260
They were bombed.

00:23:14.260 --> 00:23:15.490
The radio was destroyed.

00:23:15.490 --> 00:23:17.090
They had no communication.

00:23:17.090 --> 00:23:22.180
They didn't have Facebook
or YouTube or Twitter.

00:23:22.180 --> 00:23:23.805
I know, yeah, what
did they do all day?

00:23:23.805 --> 00:23:24.346
I don't know.

00:23:24.346 --> 00:23:25.510
They did something, yeah.

00:23:28.020 --> 00:23:28.520
Excuse me.

00:23:28.520 --> 00:23:33.850
And so the head of
Goucher College,

00:23:33.850 --> 00:23:36.820
the dean of students at
Goucher, was Dorothy Stimson,

00:23:36.820 --> 00:23:38.950
who was the first cousin
of Henry Stimson, who

00:23:38.950 --> 00:23:41.500
was the Secretary of War.

00:23:41.500 --> 00:23:43.500
And this is back in
the day, everybody.

00:23:43.500 --> 00:23:45.069
He apparently said
to her, do you

00:23:45.069 --> 00:23:47.110
have any ladies that can
come work on this thing?

00:23:47.110 --> 00:23:48.980
I can't tell you what it is.

00:23:48.980 --> 00:23:50.960
So my mom worked
on the Enigma code,

00:23:50.960 --> 00:23:53.220
which is this notorious
thing in World War II.

00:23:53.220 --> 00:23:54.950
And my whole life,
people would ask her,

00:23:54.950 --> 00:23:56.615
what did you do during the war?

00:23:56.615 --> 00:23:59.000
I can't talk about it, ha ha.

00:23:59.000 --> 00:24:00.719
I can't talk about it.

