00:37:17.950 --> 00:37:18.938
I'm sorry, man.

00:37:18.938 --> 00:37:20.420
[LAUGHTER]

00:37:20.420 --> 00:37:23.520
And you have to stay home
the rest of your life.

00:37:23.520 --> 00:37:24.530
OK, whatever.

00:37:24.530 --> 00:37:27.270
There's still bumps.

00:37:27.270 --> 00:37:30.680
And so if we found life
on Mars, for example,

00:37:30.680 --> 00:37:33.530
or stranger still, on
Europa, the moon of Jupiter

00:37:33.530 --> 00:37:36.816
with twice as much sea
water as the earth,

00:37:36.816 --> 00:37:37.940
it would change everything.

00:37:37.940 --> 00:37:38.960
I mean, I'm not saying--

00:37:38.960 --> 00:37:40.040
I said this all the time.

00:37:40.040 --> 00:37:43.160
I'm not saying we'd suddenly
drive on the left in the US.

00:37:43.160 --> 00:37:45.560
We're not going to
change everything.

00:37:45.560 --> 00:37:48.200
But it would change the way
everybody feels about being

00:37:48.200 --> 00:37:49.920
alive in the cosmos.

00:37:49.920 --> 00:37:52.050
And so that's what the
Planetary Society does.

00:37:52.050 --> 00:37:55.850
